Ports the new ACE engine (same byte-identical HalfPW NET_DATA as v10)
onto the v10 base, mirroring the browser-shipping config node-for-node:

- ZeroFence-A GHI guard (PLAIN, ghiAnchor=false): per-ply open-subtree
  dependency windows; path-dependent repetition zeros demote TT flags or
  taint the entry; tainted entries never give score cutoffs (move-only).
- RaceProof (ships ON, SPRT-passed): exact retrograde race-endgame solver
  over 81x81x2 states on the current wall graph (src/ace/race.rs), with a
  64-slot LRU keyed by wall-config zobrist, budget-gated in-tree solves,
  draw-aware eval verdicts in the RACE_MATE band, exact root solve when
  both hands are empty (depth 99), and the last-wall commitment gate with
  its deadline reserve (browser semantics: no certifier => never demote
  on missing evidence).
- wall_legal: the unsound wallCanBlockTopology gate is gone (the JS
  deleted it; its right-edge condition was the same off-by-one fixed in
  Titanium movegen) ÔÇö anchor-count precheck + own BFS only. The dead
  ACE-side topology/oracle machinery is removed with it.
- ThreatPrice and WallSense ship FALSE in the JS (falsifier-v2 /
  SPRT-killed per the source header) and are intentionally not ported.
- session keys: ace-v11, ace-v11-ti, ace-v11-ti-pmc aliases.

Validation: _vendor/acev11_parity.mjs (website repo) runs the JS engine
under node vs "titanium ace-bench" ÔÇö 14/14 positions match move, score,
depth, and EXACT node counts, covering startpos, wall fights, jump
tangles, a 24-ply line, a both-hands-empty race endgame (root solve),
and last-wall / two-left gate lines. Race tables are Bellman-validated
per config; full suite 118 passed.
